  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RDC-Ebola outbreak appeal 2021-second phase</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to reduce the risk of Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) contamination in Beni, North Kivu - DRC through warning  sensitizations sessions,community engagement and improving hygienic practice .  Affected communities will be  mobilized to consult and collaborate with Ebola response teams and reduce resistance. By applying preventives against Ebola and applied Wash practices  help prevent human to human transmission of EVD.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By the end of the project implementation period, people living in the affected areas will benefit from project&apos;s outcomes to accept and collaborate with the riposte team and minimize the resistance. Communities will adopt best practises such as  wash handing and community engagement to prevent form Ebola risk contamination.</narrative>
  </description>
